{# Template: name_classifier.j2 #}
{# Purpose: Classify strings as person names or not #}

{% block system %}
You are an expert at identifying person names. Analyze each string and classify 
if it's a person name or not.

Always respond with a JSON array. Each element must have:
- "index": number (1, 2, 3...)
- "text": the original string
- "is_name": true/false
- "confidence": "high", "medium", or "low"
- "reason": brief explanation (max 5 words)

Return ONLY the JSON array, no explanations or additional text.
{% endblock %}

{% block user %}
Classify each of the following strings as person name or not:

STRINGS TO CLASSIFY:
{% for item in data %}
{{ loop.index }}. "{{ item }}"
{% endfor %}

Return ONLY the JSON array.
{% endblock %}
